WEBVTT

00:01.661 --> 00:03.561
You really wanna ask me
who do I work for.

00:03.662 --> 00:05.462
- Fine. Who do you work for?
- Olivia Pope.

00:06.763 --> 00:08.463
Last season on Scandal.

00:08.467 --> 00:10.402
*** but this is not a law firm.

00:10.436 --> 00:11.736
We solve problems.

00:11.771 --> 00:13.988
(Abby) Manage crises,
save reputations.

00:14.023 --> 00:14.907
(Quinn) Why did she hire me?

00:15.041 --> 00:17.075
(Huck) Olivia Pope fixes things.
That's who she is.

00:17.109 --> 00:18.743
You need fixing.

00:18.778 --> 00:21.112
Everyone in this office
needs fixing.

00:21.146 --> 00:22.447
Quinn, state your name
for the record.

00:22.481 --> 00:25.116
You don't have to answer that.

00:25.150 --> 00:26.251
Her name isn't actually
Quinn Perkins.

00:26.285 --> 00:27.452
(Harrison and Abby)
Who the hell is she?

00:27.486 --> 00:28.870
(Man) Well, as far as we know,

00:28.921 --> 00:30.755
Quinn Perkins didn't
exist until 2008.

00:30.790 --> 00:32.656
(David) I'm an assistant
U.S. attorney, Liv.

00:32.674 --> 00:34.209
I prosecute crime.

00:34.260 --> 00:36.994
So at some point, even with
you, I gotta do my job.

00:37.012 --> 00:38.263
(David) I ran her prints.

00:38.297 --> 00:39.664
Don't worry.
I did it myself.

00:39.682 --> 00:41.299
Which is a good thing, because
otherwise, there would be

00:41.333 --> 00:43.668
about half a dozen U.S. agencies
looking for her.

00:43.686 --> 00:46.654
Do you want to tell them
who you are or should I?

00:46.689 --> 00:48.339
(Cyrus) You're having
an affair with Olivia Pope.

00:48.357 --> 00:49.524
I am not having...

00:49.558 --> 00:50.859
"Having," "had."
Don't Clinton me with words.

00:50.893 --> 00:53.611
Something happened
between you and Olivia.

00:53.646 --> 00:55.563
A man who isn't president
can divorce his wife.

00:55.614 --> 00:56.848
Fitz...

00:56.866 --> 00:58.900
A man who isn't president
can have a life...

00:58.951 --> 01:01.736
The life he wants,
the life he's always wanted.

01:01.787 --> 01:03.738
Some men aren't meant
to be happy.

01:03.789 --> 01:05.239
They're meant to be great.

01:05.291 --> 01:07.242
(Mellie) I'm gonna need
to take my husband back,

01:07.293 --> 01:10.194
because clearly I have to do
everything myself from now on.

01:10.212 --> 01:13.081
I was on my way, but Olivia
convinced me I was needed here,

01:13.132 --> 01:15.867
especially at such a fragile time,
given that I'm newly pregnant.

01:15.885 --> 01:17.034
(Fitz) Who are you right now?

01:17.052 --> 01:19.137
The woman who got you elected.

01:19.171 --> 01:21.256
So go be the man I voted for.

