37:05.231 --> 37:07.766
So we need to talk about...

37:07.784 --> 37:09.335
Back channel
to the east sudanese.

37:10.569 --> 37:13.605
Tell them Mellie's statement
was part of a P.R. strategy

37:13.639 --> 37:15.690
orchestrated by me to rally
the country and our allies

37:15.725 --> 37:16.942
and show that I am willing

37:16.976 --> 37:19.478
to spend every cent
of my wife's political capital...

37:19.512 --> 37:20.979
all of Fort Knox...

37:21.013 --> 37:22.264
on shutting down
his death squads

37:22.298 --> 37:23.681
and protecting our interests
in the region.

37:23.699 --> 37:25.133
Then leak it to the "Times."

37:25.168 --> 37:26.651
Use the First Lady's
press secretary,

37:26.686 --> 37:28.086
and make sure he's quoted
on record.

37:28.121 --> 37:30.322
I want her office saying
she followed my orders.

37:30.356 --> 37:31.957
It's a good plan.

37:31.991 --> 37:33.692
It'll buy you time.
It's a great plan.

37:33.726 --> 37:35.660
It's not a plan.
It's a cover.

37:35.694 --> 37:37.462
It's a lie.
It's defense...

37:37.480 --> 37:39.781
The consequence of being
sabotaged by my own wife,

37:39.816 --> 37:43.301
which I couldn't help but notice
you looked rather pleased about.

37:43.319 --> 37:44.703
It's getting awful drafty
around here, Cy...

37:44.737 --> 37:46.471
Leaks flowing out,

37:46.489 --> 37:48.072
special interests flowing in.

37:48.091 --> 37:50.242
Why am I playing defense
when that's your job?

37:50.276 --> 37:53.444
Why am I cleaning up your mess?

37:53.478 --> 37:55.478
- Mr. President...
- <i>If</i> we go to war,

37:55.514 --> 37:58.432
it's because I want
to go to war.

37:58.466 --> 37:59.750
I don't give a rat's ass

37:59.784 --> 38:01.385
if my approvals sink below
Charles Manson's,

38:01.419 --> 38:02.686
<i>no one...</i>

38:02.720 --> 38:04.805
Not you, not Mellie,
not America's baby,

38:04.839 --> 38:06.440
not the oil lobbyists...

38:06.491 --> 38:10.961
<i>No one</i> tells me when to
take this great nation to war.

38:10.995 --> 38:13.129
Am I making myself clear?

38:13.163 --> 38:14.431
- Crystal.
- Good.

38:19.854 --> 38:21.187
You want to give me
a time-out?

38:21.238 --> 38:22.872
Fine. Great.

38:22.906 --> 38:24.724
My garden's a weed patch.
I haven't seen James in weeks.

38:24.758 --> 38:26.943
I'd relish the chance
to get home before midnight.

38:26.961 --> 38:28.545
But before I go tend
to my roses,

38:28.579 --> 38:30.797
let me just say,
this plan of yours,

38:30.831 --> 38:33.049
this great plan...

38:33.083 --> 38:34.501
It's not yours.

38:34.535 --> 38:35.985
It's Olivia's.

38:36.020 --> 38:38.872
And as long as we're rewriting
our job descriptions here,

38:38.906 --> 38:41.508
keeping your wife on her leash,

38:41.542 --> 38:43.409
that's not in mine.

38:44.628 --> 38:46.429
(Door opens)

38:46.464 --> 38:49.015
(Door closes)

38:50.349 --> 38:53.235
(Camera shutter
and projector clicking)

38:53.269 --> 38:54.486
Quinn will be released
in an hour.

38:54.537 --> 38:55.837
I want a car waiting.

38:55.872 --> 38:57.973
Full security detail
at her apartment 24/7.

38:58.007 --> 38:59.424
There are protesters
outside the courthouse.

38:59.475 --> 39:01.810
We're not taking any chances.

39:01.844 --> 39:04.713
Really? We're not gonna
talk about what happened?

39:04.747 --> 39:06.815
We asked for acquittal.
Judge acquitted. It happens.

39:06.849 --> 39:07.899
No, it doesn't.

39:07.950 --> 39:09.301
The jury was set to convict.

39:09.335 --> 39:10.885
You see their faces? They were
as shocked as we were.

39:10.903 --> 39:11.920
We won this case.

39:11.954 --> 39:13.421
Mm.

39:13.455 --> 39:14.973
Quinn is going to live.

39:15.007 --> 39:19.377
Our client, a 28-year-old
girl, is going to live.

39:19.412 --> 39:21.413
And despite popular
opinion around here,

39:21.464 --> 39:25.233
<i>that</i> is a good thing.

39:26.602 --> 39:28.687
Seriously?
That trial was a joke.

39:28.721 --> 39:30.455
You know it, I know it,
Olivia knows it.

39:30.490 --> 39:31.790
And the only reason
she won't say it

39:31.824 --> 39:33.225
is 'cause she also knows
a whole hell of a lot more

39:33.259 --> 39:35.476
than she's letting on.

39:36.863 --> 39:38.547
What do you think, Huck?

39:38.581 --> 39:40.966
Ready to work across the hall
from the molotov mistress?

39:41.000 --> 39:43.885
Olivia says we trust her,
we trust her.

39:43.920 --> 39:46.387
Company man.

39:49.057 --> 39:50.357
I freaked.

39:50.392 --> 39:52.842
I checked in to the first
motel I could find.

39:52.877 --> 39:54.327
I-I needed to think.

39:54.362 --> 39:56.696
<i>And it was only hours ago</i>
<i>a deadly bomb exploded</i>

39:56.714 --> 39:59.049
<i>at Cytron Software Company,</i>

39:59.100 --> 40:00.817
<i>leaving seven dead.</i>

40:00.851 --> 40:02.752
<i>At this time,</i>
<i>the FBI and local police</i>

40:02.787 --> 40:05.505
<i>are looking for</i>
<i>possible suspect Lindsay Dwyer,</i>

40:05.539 --> 40:07.641
<i>a 26-year-old attorney who...</i>

40:07.675 --> 40:09.609
And then suddenly
someone knocked me out.

40:09.643 --> 40:11.678
<i>was romantically involved</i>
<i>with one of the victims.</i>(Grunts)

40:11.712 --> 40:14.114
<i>Of course we'll have much more</i>
<i>on this story as it develops.</i>

40:14.148 --> 40:16.616
<i>At this time...</i>

40:25.292 --> 40:27.226
(Continues typing)

40:28.044 --> 40:30.345
And a couple days later,
I woke up in a D.C. hotel

40:30.380 --> 40:33.198
with this new identity.

40:33.233 --> 40:35.417
(Gasps)

40:35.452 --> 40:37.486
Mm.

40:37.520 --> 40:39.254
(Sighs)

40:55.922 --> 40:58.073
(Quinn) When I woke up,
they were all there,

40:58.124 --> 40:59.892
just... laid out for me.

40:59.926 --> 41:01.776
A whole new life.

41:40.981 --> 41:44.767
(Projector and camera
shutter clicking)

41:51.108 --> 41:53.042
(Keyboard clicks)

41:53.077 --> 41:55.345
(Clicking)

42:24.058 --> 42:27.142
She took it,
everything we left for her.

42:27.160 --> 42:28.044
She's good to go.

42:30.180 --> 42:33.016
(Starts engine)

42:33.050 --> 42:35.184
(Gearshift clicks)

